<div id="safety" style="font-size: 28px; color: #a2a66c">
LEVEL 722 IMPORTANT SAFETY PROCEDURES
</div>
<div id="safety" style="font-size: 20px">
If you are assigned to document this level, read and understand the following procedures:
</div>
<div id="safety" style="font-size: 16px">
For "Main Level Hallway":
</div>
<div style="text-align:left;">
* 1. Don't venture too far unless you have a ''GUARANTEED'' way of returning during an unpredictable temperature change.

* 2. Avoid contact with any anomalous objects you may encounter and document them as needed.
** 2.1. This includes entities if encountered.

* 3. Do not touch the '''"C"''' under any circumstance. You will die. You will know what the '''"C"''' is when you encounter it because of its obnoxiously loud screeching noise.
** 3.1. If you are to come in close contact with the '''"C"''', contact any available medical personnel in the level immediately. You are advised to noclip to other levels to find medical personnel if none are found near you.
**3.2. You are discouraged to document the '''"C"'''. It does not need documentation.

* 4. Traverse the environment with caution. Some things may not be as they seem. Especially puddles that appear to be 2 inches deep (they are indeed not).

* 5. Always be ready to document, levels like these are no joke.

* 6. And the most important procedure, Have fun!
</div>

<div id="safety" style="font-size: 16px; color: #00a3ff">
For "Cold-Hearted Crevice":
</div>

<div style="text-align:left;">
* 1. Never traverse the crevice alone.

* 2. Keep your suit calibrated, airtight, and active at all times.

* 3. Avoid squeezing into places you do not fit in.

* 4. You are discouraged to bring any electrical equipment other than the suit with you, the equipment will short-circuit.

* 5. And again, Have fun!

</div>
<div id="safety" style="font-size: 16px; color: #ff4900">
For "This Heat, An Evil Heat Crevice":
</div>
<div style="text-align:left;">

* 1. Do not give in.

* 2. Avoid direct eye contact with the crevice, document with your peripheral vision.

* 3. If you are experiencing psychological issues, retract from the mission immediately. '''It is not worth it.'''

* 4. Do not enter the crevice under any circumstances.

* 5. Document any unusual activities within the crevice or around it.

* 6. Have another explorer with you ready to save you in case you fall victim to its urge.

* 7. Be alert at all times.
</div>
</div>


