'''Author:''' [[User:Therealimpotrrules|Choccy]]

Check History for update notes.

<span id="header" style="font-size:36px"> Some Trivia: </span>
* This level was HEAVILY inspired by ULTRAKILLs new 0-E level. The unpredictable temperatures were a byproduct.
** The name of 0-E is "This Heat, An Evil Heat" which is referenced throughout the level.
** The name of the song that plays in 0-E is called "Heart Of Cold" and the song later played is called "Dead Heat Pulse" which the level references both.

* Any inconsistencies regarding temperature is '''ON PURPOSE!''' My idea was to make everything about it feel anomalous and not even really in touch with other levels.

* The documented temperatures in the mineshaft may not make sense, but this is because the temperature is only calculated from the main mineshaft, crevice temperatures are left out to make it clearer to the reader that the main mineshaft undergoes extreme temperature changes unpredictably.

* Despite the main inspiration, I collected multiple bits and pieces from past levels that I created and merged them all into something NOT cringe, NOT cliche, and NOT childish, as I was in the past. Okay maybe a little childish.

* Level 722 used to also be owned by me, then it was replaced by a level that didn't meet standards, that level then got deleted and since then, Level 722 has not had any recreations (so far that I know of.)

* The original name of this level was going to be "Heart of Cold" but I then rethought the name due to the fact it was not necessarily cold forever. I used "Heat Pulse" to indicate how the temperature pulses up and down and causes an unsafe environment throughout the level, which is stupid, but whatever.

* My original idea, however, was making the level a Class 5e with it being constantly burning hot, I then realized I was just recreating hell, so I reworked my idea (there is no history for the past levels, I brainstormed all of this in my legitimate brain and begun putting it down on paper, or fandom wiki, I guess.)

* I might update this levels description from time to time and add changes to it that represent progress in the level, and not just making it a place that is completely impossible to explore (even though it kinda already is).

* Oh and, the idea of the "decay" was something I came up with when daydreaming about the black plague for some reason, this is true.

{{User:Therealimpotrrules/mycreations}}
